# frontend environment template
#
# Per coord/product/BOOTSTRAP_CONTRACT.md:
#   - Commit this file with placeholder values only.
#   - Real `.env` is gitignored and never committed.
#   - Load order: CI env > .env > .env.defaults > code defaults.
#   - No secrets, real credentials, or production hostnames here.
#
# Add one VAR=placeholder line per environment variable the frontend reads,
# with a one-line comment above explaining what it controls. Frontend public
# variables (commonly prefixed with PUBLIC_, NEXT_PUBLIC_, VITE_, etc.) are
# still subject to the no-secrets rule — they ship to the client.
